isSpecificAgentType` backfill block entirely. Agent type is always set correctly at session creation time.\n\n### 5. Remove nil guards added for nil agents\n\n- `strategy/common.go` `prepareTranscriptIfNeeded`: remove the `ag == nil` guard (L1454) — function already resolves agent internally from `agentType`, so this is about `GetByAgentType` failing, which won't happen for valid types.\n- Check if there are any remaining nil guards from the previous session.\n\n### 6. Update tests\n\n- **`rewind_test.go`**: Remove the `\"AgentTypeUnknown falls back to default agent\"` test case (~L223). Update empty-string test to expect an error instead of a fallback.\n- **`manual_commit_test.go`**: Remove `TestInitializeSession_BackfillsUnknownAgentType` test (~L1800-1839). Remove `AgentTypeUnknown` references from `TestSaveStep_UsesCtxAgentType_WhenPartialState`.\n\n### 7. Keep `AgentTypeUnknown` constant and switch-case usages\n\n`AgentTypeUnknown` in `agent/registry.go` stays — it's used in switch cases that treat unknown transcripts as JSONL (Claude Code format). These are format-detection patterns, not fallback logic:\n- `manual_commit_condensation.go` L250, 561, 605, 648\n- `summarize/summarize.go` L122\n- `explain.go` L550, 1551\n- `ReadAgentTypeFromTree` return value (L513)\n\nThese are correct: old checkpoints without metadata *should* be parsed as Claude Code JSONL.\n\n## Files to modify\n\n1. `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go` — remove `DefaultAgentType`, `isSpecificAgentType`, simplify `resolveAgentType`, remove nil guard from `prepareTranscriptIfNeeded`\n2. `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_rewind.go` — simplify `ResolveAgentForRewind`\n3. `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — remove backfill logic\n4. `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/rewind_test.go` — update tests\n5. `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_test.go` — remove backfill tests\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\n```\n\n\nIf you need specific detail